This paper is about text generation using generative adversarial networks (GANs), which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of autoencoders (AEs) and hybrid approaches, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) research (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image captioning, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of GANs for discrimination, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE).
